snippet.textDisplay:
I just wanted to take a moment and appreciate your willingness to be open about your opinions and so many things people will censor themselves on because they don't want to risk losing subscribers or people in general not liking them because of being "controversial".

In your videos, you talk so casually and candidly about sex&sexuality, social and psychological issues, periods and the experience of being a woman, feeling lonely or disoriented, depressed, confused, unsure, insecure, scared, intimidated, all feelings that although you often make them into self-deprecating jokes, you also address them in a serious fashion, in little talks with us, and I really appreciate it.

I couldn't be that brave with such a large audience and with the pressure of being liked being part of you making a living, so I really want to take a moment and appreciate your willingness to be that open and vulnerable, it really means a lot to me to see it-it inspires me to be more comfortable, confident, and assertive myself, more honest with myself and unapologetic, and sometimes I absorb your attitude just through watching you.
I don't think you'll see this comment and it doesn't really matter if you don't. It's just something I felt needed to be said. Thank you! :)
